{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-6120"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Community Mobile Network Infrastructure Operations"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "6120"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :communication/wireless-network-operator
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:connectivity :digital-inclusion :spectrum-stewardship]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :mobile-network-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :phone]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:optimization]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "Network Operations Advisor ⊣ Mobile Network Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph (langgraph.graph, wirelesstelecom.operation/build),
 append-only audit ledger (wirelesstelecom.store/ledger +
 append-ledger!, MemStore and a DatomicStore backed by langchain.db via
 langchain-store.core). Compiled StateGraph
 (:intake -> :advise -> :govern -> :decide -+-> :commit /
 :request-approval -> :commit / :hold) with
 `interrupt-before #{:request-approval}` + in-memory checkpointer for
 real human-in-the-loop resume, proven end-to-end by
 `test/wirelesstelecom/operation_test.cljc`. The primary entity is a
 registered SITE (cell tower / base station), analogous to a field in
 the sibling tobacco-growing coordinator (cloud-itonami-isic-0115) --
 the reference template this build follows -- carrying a structural
 `:spectrum-license-status` and `:site-access-record`. Seven ops, all
 `:effect :propose` only: `:log-network-build-record` (robotics-
 assisted tower/base-station deployment or maintenance record),
 `:schedule-site-operation`, `:activate-tower` (HARD: the site's OWN
 recorded spectrum-license-status must be :active), `:provision-
 subscriber` (HARD: the site's OWN recorded site-access-record must be
 present), `:log-billing-record` (HARD: usage-evidence must be cited),
 `:flag-network-fault` (ALWAYS escalates to a human network operator --
 covers equipment failure/interference/structural concerns and the
 safety-critical out-of-band/tower-climb/high-voltage site work this
 repo's own README names), and `:order-equipment` (cost-threshold
 escalation). Two permanently blocked ops (`:operate-tower-equipment`,
 `:finalize-spectrum-license-decision`) -- direct radio/tower-equipment
 actuation and spectrum-license grant/renewal/revocation decisions stay
 categorically outside this back-office coordinator's authority, no
 override. 49 tests / 183 assertions green (`clojure -M:dev:test`),
 clj-kondo 0 errors, demo runnable end-to-end against both Store
 backends (`clojure -M:dev:run`).

 CORRECTION HISTORY (see `docs/adr/0002-site-spectrum-scope-
 correction.md`): an earlier same-day implementation attempt on this
 repo (i) mirrored the WRONG sibling actor 'op-for-op' -- its own
 ADR-0001 Decision 1 states it copied `cloud-itonami-isic-6190` (the
 VoIP/reseller sibling that this repo's own README explicitly
 distinguishes itself from: 6190 'does not own spectrum or network
 infrastructure') -- producing a subscriber-identity/MSISDN-
 provisioning model with ZERO site/tower/spectrum-license-status/
 robotics modeling despite this blueprint's own `:robotics true` and
 README `Robotics premise` paragraph; and (ii) fabricated jurisdiction-
 specific regulatory citations (a Japanese Radio Act / MIC citation, a
 US Communications Act of 1934 / FCC citation, a UK Wireless Telegraphy
 Act / Ofcom citation, a German TKG / Bundesnetzagentur citation) in
 `wirelesstelecom.facts` that were NOT present anywhere in this repo's
 own pre-existing published docs and were not independently verified.
 It also had a broken `deps.edn` (stale, no-longer-existing
 `com-junkawasaki/langgraph-clj`/`langchain-clj` paths), hand-rolled its
 own EDN-blob codec instead of using `kotoba-lang/langchain-store`
 (ADR-2607141600), and had no CI workflow and no test that ever
 exercised the compiled StateGraph end-to-end. This implemented-slice
 replaces that attempt: `wirelesstelecom.facts` now carries only
 structural, non-jurisdiction-specific reference data (build-status
 vocabulary, equipment-procurement categories, site-operation-type
 reference set); the site/spectrum-license/site-access domain layer
 that was the actual differentiator is now implemented; `deps.edn`
 points at the current `kotoba-lang/langgraph`/`langchain`/
 `langchain-store`; the Store uses `langchain-store.core`; CI
 (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`, sibling-checkout pattern) and
 `test/wirelesstelecom/operation_test.cljc` are added."}
